<topic id="customizing_the_author_visual_editing_mode">
    <title>Customizing the Author visual editing mode</title>
    <body>
        <p>The <b>Author</b> visual editing mode is based on CSS: <xref
                href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/doc/ug-editor/topics/dg-css-support-in-author.html"
                format="html" scope="external"/>. Besides supporting most of the CSS 3
            specification, Oxygen adds some custom CSS selectors, properties and functions: <xref
                href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/doc/ug-editor/topics/dg-oXygen-css-extensions.html"
                format="html" scope="external"/>. Here are some of the most interesting
            additions:</p>
        <ul id="ul_mtl_5xr_rgb">
            <li>
                <p>Use CSS selectors to match XML comments, processing instructions, entities and
                    CDATA sections: <xref
                        href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/doc/ug-editor/topics/dg-additional-custom-selectors.html"
                        format="html" scope="external"/></p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Change the tags display mode and tags color for certain elements: <xref
                        href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/doc/ug-editor/topics/dg-css-additional-properties.html"
                        format="html" scope="external"/></p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Mark certain XML elements as not editable: <xref
                        href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/doc/ug-editor/topics/dg-css-additional-properties.html"
                        format="html" scope="external"/></p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Lots of custom CSS functions, of which the <b>oxy_xpath</b> function allowing you
                    to run an XPath over the document and use that value as static text: <xref
                        href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/doc/ug-editor/topics/dg-oxygen-css-functions.html"
                        format="html" scope="external"/></p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>You can match in the CSS custom pseudo class values which can be changed via a
                    custom Author action: <xref
                        href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/doc/ug-editor/topics/dg-custom-css-pseudo-classes.html"
                        format="html" scope="external"/>.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>There are specific @media types which can be used to mark certain CSS sections
                    for a certain Oxygen distribution: <xref
                        href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/doc/ug-editor/topics/dg-oxygen-media-type.html"
                        format="html" scope="external"/>.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Fonts can be dynamically loaded and used for rendering: <xref
                        href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/doc/ug-editor/topics/dg-font-face-media.html"
                        format="html" scope="external"/>.</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </body>
</topic>
